Sydney was my friend Mandy’s cat. She lived to be the ripe old age of 18 (at least!) We’re not exactly sure how old she was. Most of you know that I’m pretty much a dog person, but I have loved a few cats in my life. Sydney was one of those special ones. When I would go over to Mandy’s house, if I was there for coffee talk, or just hanging out, it wouldn’t take long for Sydney to make her way to me and lay right in the middle of my laptop, or snuggle up against me and let me pet her. Syd and I were buddies. This year, Sydney became a cover girl for the launch of TY Cat Food. One of my favorite things about Sydney is that expression on her face, that basically said, “Yeah, I know I’m cool”…and she was. 
Losing a pet is gut-wrenching. Most of us have been there and know the pain and loss all too well. But in the end, I would choose the unconditional love and joy that pets bring, knowing that the loss will eventually come, over not having these wonderful animals in our lives. Sending all of our love and comfort to Mandy. Thank you Sydney, for making our lives better. xoxo Trisha

Don’t forget to comment the name of your favorite @TrishaYearwood song at @CountryMusicHOF by October 17 for a chance to win big. The Country Music Hall of Fame and Museum has partnered with the Nashville Symphony to give away two tickets to Yearwood's October 20 performance, two tickets to the Museum, and a copy of her newest cookbook, "Trisha's Kitchen." Trisha Yearwood performs at the Symphony October 19-21. Visit the link in @CountryMusicHOF’s bio for official giveaway rules.

Did this night really happen?! To say I had the time of my life in Austin is an understatement. 

I feel humbled to be honored on such a sacred stage. Live music can change people’s lives and what Austin City Limits has been doing for live music for the last 50 years is truly life changing, not only for the artists and the players, but most importantly for everyone watching and listening.

Thank you @brothersosborne, @jodeemessina, @thebrandyclark and @ronniedunn for sharing such a special night with me. Many thanks to @officiallymcconaughey and to the love of my life, Garth Brooks for your special words. 

And Don Henley, this honor will forever mean that much more because you welcomed me into the @acltv Hall of Fame. Appreciate you, my friend!

What a night!! xo
